From yixuan.qiu at cos.name  Wed Nov 26 08:13:58 2014
From: yixuan.qiu at cos.name (Yixuan Qiu)
Date: Wed, 26 Nov 2014 02:13:58 -0500
Subject: [Rcpp-devel] Rcpp: Modification of input argument: Undefined
	behaviour
In-Reply-To: <1416983602849.66418@mail.utoronto.ca>
References: <1416983602849.66418@mail.utoronto.ca>
Message-ID: <CAFr_7yF26U7ZQuuNyghK7BZgsPUnq4dek9BV7D6Y8iJfD9H_yg@mail.gmail.com>

Hello David,
The general answer to your question is, if the type of your matrix (integer
or numeric) in R is different from the one you declare in Rcpp, Rcpp will
make a copy and cast it to the appropriate type.
For example, 1:12 is of type integer, and if you pass it as a
NumericMatrix, Rcpp will implicitly copy the whole matrix, so no matter
what modification you did, the original matrix will not change.

Best,
Yixuan
